---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service - Domain Echo | Free Chat Extension"
  description="Domain Echo Terms of Service: Read our terms for using the free anonymous chat extension. Simple, fair terms for a privacy-first service."
  keywords="terms of service, user agreement, chat extension terms, domain echo legal"
  canonicalUrl="/terms"
>
  <section class="py-20 bg-gradient-to-b from-slate-950 to-slate-900">
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 max-w-4xl">
      <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-6 bg-gradient-to-r from-white to-purple-400 bg-clip-text text-transparent">
        Terms of Service
      </h1>
      <p class="text-slate-400 mb-8">Last updated: February 9, 2026</p>

      <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none space-y-8">
        <div class="bg-slate-900 p-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Agreement to Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            By installing and using Domain Echo, you agree to be bound by these Terms of Service. If you don't agree to these terms, please don't use Domain Echo.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 p-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Description of Service</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Domain Echo is a Chrome browser extension that provides anonymous, real-time chat rooms for every website domain you visit. The service allows users to communicate with others who are currently visiting the same domain.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 p-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">User Conduct</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            You agree to use Domain Echo responsibly and not to:
          </p>
          <ul class="text-slate-300 space-y-2">
            <li>❌ Post illegal, harmful, threatening, abusive, harassing, defamatory, or otherwise objectionable content</li>
            <li>❌ Impersonate any person or entity</li>
            <li>❌ Spam, flood, or disrupt the service</li>
            <li>❌ Attempt to hack, reverse engineer, or compromise the service</li>
            <li>❌ Collect or harvest personal information about other users</li>
            <li>❌ Use the service for any illegal purpose</li>
            <li>❌ Post content that infringes on intellectual property rights</li>
            <li>❌ Share malicious links or malware</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 p-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Content and Moderation</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            You are solely responsible for the content you post through Domain Echo. We reserve the right to remove any content that violates these terms or is otherwise inappropriate.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            While we strive to maintain a safe environment, we cannot monitor all conversations in real-time. If you encounter inappropriate content, please report it.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 p-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Anonymity and Privacy</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Domain Echo provides anonymous chat through randomly generated usernames. However, you should not assume complete anonymity. Do not share personal information in chat rooms.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            Please review our <a href="/privacy" class="text-indigo-400 hover:text-indigo-300">Privacy Policy</a> for more information about how we handle data.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 p-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Domain Echo and its original content, features, and functionality are owned by Domain Echo and are protected by international copyright, trademark, and other intellectual property laws.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 p-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            Domain Echo is provided "AS IS" and "AS AVAILABLE" without warranties of any kind, either express or implied. We do not guarantee that the service will be uninterrupted, secure, or error-free.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 p-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, Domain Echo shall not be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages resulting from your use of or inability to use the service.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 p-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Termination</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            We reserve the right to terminate or suspend access to Domain Echo immediately, without prior notice, for any reason, including breach of these Terms.
          </p>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed mt-4">
            You may stop using Domain Echo at any time by uninstalling the extension.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 p-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Changes to Terms</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            We reserve the right to modify these terms at any time. We will notify users of any material changes by updating the "Last updated" date. Continued use of Domain Echo after changes constitutes acceptance of the new terms.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 p-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Governing Law</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            These Terms shall be governed by and construed in accordance with the laws of the jurisdiction in which Domain Echo operates, without regard to its conflict of law provisions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-slate-900 p-8 rounded-xl border border-slate-800">
          <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Contact Us</h2>
          <p class="text-slate-300 leading-relaxed">
            If you have questions about these Terms of Service, please contact us at:
          </p>
          <p class="text-indigo-400 mt-2">
            legal@domainecho.com
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

